Uganda secured 500 billion shillings
in loans from the African Development Bank and the Japan
International Cooperation Agency to boost power distribution,
the Daily Monitor said, citing Uganda Electricity Transmission
Co. Ltd.  The money will be used to build transmission lines in the
western, eastern and northern parts of the country next year,
the Kampala-based newspaper reported, citing Elias Kiyemba, the
agencyâ€™s managing director. It gave no further details about the
